This paper discusses fairness in algorithmic decision-making processes, which is a topic that falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the social outcomes of different fairness criteria, which could also be relevant to the categories of cybernetics (cs.CY), cryptography and security (cs.CR), social and information networks (cs.SI), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
